Package: pathtree
Type: Package
Title: Pathway Trees and Predictive Pathway Discovery in Sequence Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Mohammed",
           family = "Saqr",
           email = "saqr@saqr.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Discovers, ranks, and interprets predictive pathways in
    categorical sequence data. Fits a variable-depth pathway tree
    (prediction suffix tree; Ron, Singer and Tishby (1996)
    <doi:10.1023/A:1026490906255>) and exposes a pathway-centric API:
    most common pathways, most predictively divergent pathways,
    sharpest pathways, modal-flip diagnostics, and next-state
    predictions. Multiple pruning criteria (likelihood-ratio G^2,
    Kullback-Leibler, AIC, BIC), smoothing for unseen contexts, and
    sequence sampling are supported. Validated to machine precision
    against the archived 'PST' package (Gabadinho and Ritschard,
    2013).
